{
  "texts": [
    "Simpson et al.",
    "expand the IPCC approach by incorporating a fourth risk determinant: the response (R), which refers to existing measures that counteract or mitigate risk.",
    "They also contextualise risk assessment by including multiple types of risk with their own determinants.",
    "Thus, according to their framework, the overall risk results from the interaction among (1) determinants, (2) drivers, and (3) risk types (Fig. 2).",
    "These three sets of relations occur at stages of increasing complexity."
  ]
}